<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-224-904  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 224 904.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  March 1 1990 n1203 p28(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Components of a common goal. (Lucas Industries wins award foremployee training program)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Haughton, Emma.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Engineering company Lucas Industries is the winner of ComputerWeekly's sixth annual training award.andP;  Lucas has more than 60,000employees, half of whom work abroad, and the company's divisionsall operate autonomously.andP;  The company's Management ServicesCareer Development Scheme, which bridges business and computing,encourages staff to manage their own professional training anddevelopment.andP;  The scheme's three main sections are businessawareness and skills, personal and managerial skills, andprofessional and functional skills.andP;  Training includes seminars,internal and external courses, and modules on such skills asquality assurance, project control, and statistics.andP;  Lucascontinually evaluates its training program, reports favorablefeedback from trainees, and believes the program has easedrecruitment and retention problems and led to higher productivity.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lucas Industries PLC (training).andO;Topic:     Achievements and AwardsTraining of Employees.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>